    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Pump Assembly - Assembly</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>All the valves must drop into their bores freely without hanging up.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the converter clutch control valve, cooler bypass valve and thermostat valve,
                converter pressure limit valve, converter anti-drain back valve and the main regulator valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010288" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0066469.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the main regulator boost valve spring, plug and install the retainer
                    clip.
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the converter anti-drain back valve, spring, plug and install the
                    retainer clip.
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the converter pressure limit valve, spring, plug and install the
                    retainer clip.
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the thermostat spring and valve.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the cooler bypass valve, plug and clip.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Install the converter clutch control valve, spring, plug and install the
                    retainer clip.
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Prior to installation, lightly lubricate the pump gears with clean automatic transmission fluid.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the gearotor gearset with both dots facing up.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010289" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0066470.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tool, measure the pump gear to pump body clearance.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010290" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0018748.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the separator plate.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010291" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0057640.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Prior to pump assembly, make sure all cup plugs are installed.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Inspect mating surfaces of the pump body and the control body to make sure they are clean and free
                    of nicks and burrs.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Note the location of the alignment pins. The pins should be installed at 1 o'clock and 7 o'clock
                    with the pump filter inlet sump at 6 o'clock. The alignment pins should move freely when installing
                    the band strap.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tools, assemble the control body and stator assembly onto the pump body.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010292" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0018749.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure that the outer edges of the pump body and the outer bolt holes are aligned during
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the pump and loosely install the bolts. Check that the outer edges of the pump body
                and the bolt holes are aligned.
            </para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 29 Nm (21 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010293" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0057639.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate and install a new overdrive piston.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010294" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0057638.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the overdrive piston return spring and the bolts.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 29 Nm (21 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010295" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0057637.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new pump seals.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010296" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0005658.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the seal with automatic transmission fluid and install the pump outer diameter
                square-cut front pump seal with the white stripe facing out.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010297" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0057636.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new front pump seal, using the special tool.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010298" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0018750.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new front pump stator support seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010299" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDD0/DD0314A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lightly lubricate the thrust washer and the bearing with petroleum jelly to hold them in place
                    during assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the No. 1 pump thrust washer and the No. 2A overdrive sun gear thrust bearing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010300" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0006629.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
